Guy T. HELVERING, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, Petitioner on Review, v. The WARREN TELEPHONE COMPANY, Respondent on Review. No. 8451. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 10, 1939. Samuel O. Clark, Jr., Asst. Atty. Gen., J. P. Wenchel, of Washington, D. C., and Sewall Key, Sp. Asst. to Atty. Gen., for petitioner. H. H. Hoppe, of Warren, Ohio, for respondent.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the motion to dismiss this cause, filed herein by the petitioner on review, and it appearing that counsel for the respondent on review has consented to the granting thereof:

It is, by the Court, adjudged and ordered that this cause be, and is hereby dismissed, without costs to either party.
